column5: Headed up to Big Cliff's yesterday to help put his dock in. Daniel and I arrived there at 10:30. Pikeslayer(Simon), Pikeslayer jr(Sean) and his friend(Jordan) arrived at 11:00. We started on the dock and about 2 1/2 hours later we were done and having a good lunch made by Cliff's wife Sue and Simon's wife Mary. I don't know what she calls those tasty things she made but they were ham.green onion,light cream cheese in a wrap!! Damn they were good!!!!!!!!!!  :thumbsup_anim:  Daniel was in charge of picture taking, in between helping us with the dock. Here's the pictures he took, Simon has a few he can add too.  Simon fixing the dock   Sean fixing another piece of dock along with Cliff   The first section.   Waiting for the next section.   Checking to make sure the boat had clearance from the dock.   The final piece was in and we are off to get lunch.   Many hands make for light work. It was a good fun day, had by all. With the exemption of Jordan who was jumping in the water with his bathing suit on to help me level the section, every time he jumped in as a man, when he got out he was almost a woman....LOL  Daniel sends a big thank you to you Cliff for the engines.

Well dang it all...I meant to drop down to play supervisor but got tied up with getting the groceries for today's Easter dinner and then some yard work clearing brush and it completely slipped my mind As my old pal Nanook used to say..."it's me age...don't you know!").....  Last dock party at Cliff's, Jack and I couldn't do much about the docks but we managed to burn some pretty swell burgers... Damn I miss him...
Right on--Yet another place to pitch for bass  Just kiddin---looks good
Looks great ! Another OFC Community team effort.
Never mind Bass...it makes a good carp "swim"...
Great stuff, OFC pulling together to make a project happen and enjoy each other's company
Great job Skeet Kudos to you and all involved
See also, "OFNrs, they just don't get any better"! Best people in the world!
Awe shucks Cliff...you only say that 'cause it's true...
